  "text": "Programmed cell death (apoptosis) in NASH and other chronic liver diseases promotes tissue injury and fibrosis [CITATION_1] , which establishes a rationale for inhibiting apotosis as a therapeutic strategy. Emricasan, a pancaspase inhibitor, reduces apoptosis that can attenuate inflammation and fibrosis [CITATION_2] ; it is also currently in phase 2B clinical trials for NASH (NCT02686762).",
